A discarded employee took revenge, bought laptops for the company and sold them
After his release, the disgraced employee bought computers for the company and then sold them.
He spent the money before the arrest of the police.
Within a short period of time, the man purchased a total of sixteen computers for more than two hundred thousand crowns.
"He took the laptops to Olomouc after the takeover, where he sold them after bazaars," said Rostislav Brückner, the senior commissioner of the Šumperk Police.
The motive for the fraud was revenge on the employer for the release and also the profit of money.
"In questioning, he told us that he used the money for loan repayments," Brückner said.
Police also found that the fraudster was a pathological player who was repeatedly treated in psychiatry.
The money could also end up in winning devices or video lottery terminals.
"The fact is, we didn't find any money with him," the commissioner said.
A fraudster, who has already been punished once for theft, is now facing a prison term of one to five years.
Police have not yet said whether there is also a risk of punishment for the bazaars that bought the laptops under the price and continued to sell them.
"It is true that they took over completely new goods, which is at least suspicious," the commissioner said.
However, none of the owners of the bazaar have been charged.
